    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="858"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d858">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/350.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Special Representative</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 27 and April 9. The bankers are satisfied with the report from
                    Monrovia, and you may now proceed with negotiations with the bondholders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
